Path: This week in Nu #71
Content:
ymgyt updated the 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell.github.io/pull/79] Japanese translation of the Nushell book
baoyachi removed 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2827] some unused code
stormasm has been 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2828] refactoring nu-cli to make it simpler
 (also 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2831] here
 and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2833] here
)
fdncred changed 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2829] ``ls``
 to output a path for the name
max-sixty simplified 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2830] the internal run_block functionality
, and updated the 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell.github.io/pull/78] docs for explaining pipelines and groups
ArturKovacs replaced 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2832] 'clipboard' with the newer 'arboard' crate
LhKipp extended 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2834] 'which' to show aliases and custom commands
JosephTLyons fixed 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2835] all the new Rust 1.49 linting warnings
jonathandturner fixed 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2836] the 
``source``
 command to properly error
 (
[link: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=pBOZpyqldZQ] video available
), and fixed 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2837] commands created inside of other commands to not leak out to the global scope
